        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Chronicles 26:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and Shallum 9:19) received by lot the post of honour on the east side of the Sanctuary.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Then for Zechariah his son.—Heb., And Zechariah his son, counselling with sagacity, they cast lots. The preposition for may have fallen out before Zechariah; or perhaps Zechariah is the real subject of the verb “cast lots,” which is plural, because Zechariah is the name of a clan or guild. (Comp. 1Chronicles 24:31; xxv, 8). Zechariah, the firstborn of Meshelemiah (1Chronicles 26:2), obtained the charge of the north side “They cast lots” may mean drew a lot from the urn.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Then for Zechariah his son.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Heb., ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "And Zechariah his son, counselling with sagacity, they cast lots.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " The preposition ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "for",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " may have fallen out before ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Zechariah;",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " or perhaps Zechariah is the real subject of the verb “cast lots,” which is plural, because Zechariah is the name of a clan or guild. (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 24:31",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; xxv, 8). Zechariah, the firstborn of Meshelemiah (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 26:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "), obtained the charge of the north side “They cast lots” may mean drew a lot from the urn.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A wise counsellor.—This little touch is obviously a mark of truth. The chronicler could have had no motive for so characterising a warder of the Temple, unless he had found it in some older source, of which he has only given extracts.",
        "children": [
          {
